  "body": "<!--💎💎💎💎💎💎💎💎💎💎💎💎💎💎💎💎💎💎💎💎💎💎💎💎💎💎💎💎\r\n\r\nHellooo! 😄 \r\n\r\nTo help us tend to your issue faster, please search our currently open issues before submitting a new one.\r\nExisting issues often contain information about workarounds, resolution, or progress updates.\r\n\r\n💎💎💎💎💎💎💎💎💎💎💎💎💎💎💎💎💎💎💎💎💎💎💎💎💎💎💎💎💎💎💎-->\r\n\r\n# 💎 Cannot open JWT secret file\r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\n<!-- ✍️--> Hello, I'm trying to sync my own Ethereum fullnode after the merge. I decided to use prysm beacon node and I constantly get the error:\r\n```\r\n[2022-09-28 18:01:47] ERROR main: could not read JWT secret file for authenticating execution API: open /root/jwtsecret: no such file or directory\r\n```\r\n\r\nI've got no clue why it's happening. If I run my geth execution client it works just fine (it says loaded jwtsecret succesfully). Only when I try to use the consensus client I get the error. Obviously there is a *jwtsecret* file at `/root/` directory\r\n\r\nMy run command is:\r\n\r\n```\r\ndocker run -it -v $HOME/.eth2:/data -p 4000:4000 -p 13000:13000 -p 12000:12000/udp --name beacon-node \\\r\n  gcr.io/prysmaticlabs/prysm/beacon-chain:stable \\\r\n  --datadir=/data \\\r\n  --jwt-secret=/root/jwtsecret \\\r\n  --rpc-host=0.0.0.0 \\\r\n  --grpc-gateway-host=0.0.0.0 \\\r\n  --monitoring-host=0.0.0.0 \\\r\n  --execution-endpoint=/root/.ethereum/geth.ipc\r\n  ```\r\n",
